    "body" : "<p>Taken from the <a href=\"http://java.sun.com/javase/6/docs/technotes/tools/windows/javadoc.html#@see\" rel=\"noreferrer\">javadoc spec</a></p>\n\n<p><code>@see &lt;a href=\"URL#value\"&gt;label&lt;/a&gt;</code> :\nAdds a link as defined by <code>URL#value</code>. The <code>URL#value</code> is a relative or absolute URL. The Javadoc tool distinguishes this from other cases by looking for a less-than symbol (<code>&lt;</code>) as the first character. </p>\n\n<p>For example : <code>@see &lt;a href=\"http://www.google.com\"&gt;Google&lt;/a&gt;</code></p>\n"
  }, {
