    "answer_id" : 31974320,
    "question_id" : 1082050,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Javadocs don't offer any special tools for external links, so you should just use standard html:</p>\n\n<pre><code>See &lt;a href=\"http://groversmill.com/\"&gt;Grover's Mill&lt;/a&gt; for a history of the\nMartian invasion.\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>or</p>\n\n<pre><code>@see &lt;a href=\"http://groversmill.com/\"&gt;Grover's Mill&lt;/a&gt; for a history of \nthe Martian invasion.\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Don't use <code>{@link ...}</code> or <code>{@linkplain ...}</code> because these are for links to the javadocs of other classes and methods.</p>\n"
  } ],
